                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_107017">Aston Rowant (Oxon.)</placeName>.
                             
                            <persName nymRef="Chalcford">
                           <forename>Roger</forename> son of <surname>Peter</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_107024">Chalcford</placeName>
                        </persName> grants to <orgName key="org_107004">W<supplied>allingford</supplied>
                        </orgName> in free alms a croft called <placeName type="minor">Chalfcroft</placeName> in <placeName key="place_107024">Chalcford</placeName>, except a third part which <persName>
                           <forename>Isowde</forename>, mother of <persName>
                              <forename>William</forename> the <surname>marshal</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> holds in dower. Rent 12<hi rend="italic">d.</hi> For this the monks gave him 2½ marks.
                            Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> of <surname>Gingestone</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Adam</forename> of <surname>Copicote</surname>
                        </persName>,
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename> the <surname>clerk</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Hugh</forename> of <surname>Stockenechun</surname>
                        </persName> ..., 
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Auger</forename> de la <surname>Redelan</surname>’</persName>, 
                            <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Melesop</surname>
                        </persName>, 
